I suppose when you drop an entire mountain a few feet, it amounts
to more than a little energy.

A lot of underground coal mines use columns of coal to hold up
the roof in the seam being worked.  This places tremendous
compressive loads on the columns; the practice sounds insanely
dangerous.  It's mentioned in the book/movie &quot;October Sky&quot; as
feeling like an earthquake, and the column failures are literally
explosive.

